caption: 5 star Service, Great food.
Great Service, Great food. Almost left my takeout box there and thus nice lady working went out and brought it out to me before I got to my car. 10/10
Food was amazing, staff was wonderful even though we were there late.
The food is amazing.  Everything seems to be hand made and definitely made with love.  Would most definitely, 100%, undoubtedly recommend.
The food is always amazing and the service is always fast and COVID-conscious. Couldn't ask for a better neighborhood spot!
Good soup

The Thai Beef Salad with cilantro, basil, red onion, basil, and the list goes on. Words don't do this salad justice, but I'm going to try to explain the experience. The flavors are impeccably matched. The crunch from the texture of the crisped rice over the beef meets the lime juice to create heaven in your mouth. If you like cilantro, now you're not coming down form this food high. The lettuce isn't soggy or oily. I'll never stop ordering this dish as long as I'm in the area.
Fried rice is tasty and worth it!
Good and friendly. For lovers of spicy food, you choose the hotness from a 5 point scale. 3 was decently spicy for me, and I'm someone who is used to strong chilis.
Pleasant staff and food is consistently good.
Fantastic Asian American and Thai cuisine. It's a step above your usual hum-drum takeout place, but not much more expensive
Well priced, and good selection of lunch specials. Ask about large togo orders, don't cook for a week! (but double check what freezes well)

If you are a sushi lover, I highly recommend this restaurant. I don't understand why the sushi in a Thai restaurant is far much better than those in Japanese restaurant. The fish is fresh, the rice is perfectly flavoured and sticky enough to be dipped into the soya sauce without being broken, although the piece of rice is a bit too big to my mouth. The pad Thai, pad wood sen and pad thai wood sen are delicious, too. Fried tofu and steamed mussels are also tasty. I've been a loyal customer of this restaurant and never disappointed about the food. However, I don't recommend the soup because most of them are so bland.

Siam Terrace is a bit on the expensive side, but once you taste their food you won't regret it. I have never had a meal here that wasn't fresh and flavorful. I particularly recommend the Mussamun Curry, Firecracker Chicken, Pineapple Fried Rice, and Crispy Pad Thai. The Crispy Pad Thai is a unique twist on traditional Pad Thai that uses crispy wonton chips instead of noodles. Delicious!
My favorite place to get thai! I love the options on their menu and how easy it is to order online. Highly recommend!

Can do with better service. Food is excellent - everything we have tried we have loved. The staff is not helpful and at one point straight doubted us when we asked for different plates as the ones gives to us were dirty, literally smelling the plates in front of us. The restaurant was empty, you could just give us different plates. Given that they charge tip by default - it would be great if they actually try and give better service.
Best overall Thai restaurant in the area!
They have pretty good sushi, too!
Great Thai food and sushi plus excellent staff!

I’ve been going to Siam Terrace since it opened. It’s where I always take my out of town guests. It’s the best Thai food in town, the service is great, they are very friendly, and the prices are very reasonable. It’s my #1 restaurant.
Great food, and amazing staff. Fantastic local business

Had the spring rolls and jungle curry with tofu. All the veggies were super fresh, tofu was not too soft. Jungle curry was a little spicy but not overpowering. Dish overall had super clean taste. Bit pricey but would recommend.
Found a roach in my food gross then the owner yelled at me about it gross place
Great food!

I am disappointed that my gift certificate wasn’t fully honored. We are in a global pandemic and COVID hasn’t gone anywhere and is beginning to spike. With all that is going on, I didn’t realize I missed the expiration date by 24 hours. I asked the waitress to ask if there was any grace period to honor the full amount, and she said “knowing the owner, he won’t allow it.” I then asked her to inquire any way because we are living through unprecedented times, and surely he could make an exception.  She returned and said the owner would not allow it. I eat her often, and this is the only Thai restaurant I like. Based on the unwillingness and inflexibility of the owner, I will not return! He or she could have definitely made an exception, and it wasn’t like I came in with something that had been expired for days or weeks.  The owner never came to the front, and it appeared he or she couldn’t care less. While I hope cases don’t rise, but if we have to go back to phase 1, possibly the owner can work on better customer relations while closed. I will seek other options, and tell everyone I know, which is a vast group of people, about my less than optimal experience.

So nice and professional. I order from them all the time and if I ever get a wrong order ( which happens so rarely and I have a special diet) they provide me with replacements. I am always happy to see when their restaurant is full
Love it
Extra dollar for the sauce wasn’t worth it. Also My stomach is hurting!
Loved it
Nice service. The food is good. Been there twice now. They are also open till 10 pm, so great option if you live in downtown Urbana, and say are returning late from work.

Ordered a couple entrees for take out, and found the whole online ordering - carry out service to be efficient. The food itself was very good - but not excellent. Seemed to have too many vegetables in the yellow curry. The sticky rice was delicious though! Specifically requested cutlery for 2 people, but received just one spoon and one fork. Would probably eat here again to see if we can hit the 5 star experience.
Good food and friendly but took forever this time
Enjoyed the food
Very disappointed. Spent $40.00 on delivery requests all sauces but didn’t get what I asked for 😤

I ordered some food in. I ordered Kani Su, Dragon Roll, Thai iced tea, and sticky rice with custard. The Kani Su was pretty good. The Dragon Roll was so/so, not my favorite but not horrible. The Thai ice tea was good. Sadly the sticky rice with custard was not good. The rice was all once piece and even with fingers I could not separate it. Also the custard tasted off. I didn't eat much of it. This place has many good reviews so I am willing to try it again in the future but not anytime soon.
My favorite Thai place in town!
Tom yum soup is so good!

Poor quality premises...full of mosquitoes. I swatted two mosquitoes and showed the server after placing order and he said there’s nothing they could do! Food was mediocre...avoid the spicy catfish dish that’s served in a ridiculous presentation lined with broccoli in a crooked, unappetizing triangular shape. Green curry with medium spice turned out to be outrageously spicy. The chef is not Thai...go figure!
One of our favorite local restaurants
The crab Rangoon is the best ever - ethereally light and crispy! The Pad Thai was a little disappointing, not as good as it used to be.

This is hands down the best sushi in the area! Everytime we go in to eat the service is timely and efficient, the sushi is consistent and amazing! Such a friendly relaxed atmosphere. Love this place. Great thai dishes as well. I suggest the pad thai or any of the fried rice dishes! Sushi i suggest the twin towers! A must try!
Yummy.  Great Thai food for vegetarians!
Probably my favorite restaurant in town. Super low key and I've loved everything I've ever ordered from there.

I dined here with three friends on a Saturday night this January and we enjoyed prompt service and truly delicious food. The portions were plenty, but not too much for a single meal, and the prices for each of our entrees varied between ~$9-$13. I would go here again.
There food is always amazing.
Good food and service.
Chiang Mai Noodles with Chicken is my favorite

One of my favorite places to go. Three of our children came with tonight, my daughter said this was the best sushi she's ever had! Everyone loved their meal choice, they'll definitely be coming back now too!

It was all very average Thai food. My summer rolls and young papaya salad was good. The vegetable soup was ok. My entree was my least favorite dish which was a vegetable dish with a peanut sauce. The ambiance is decent.
Love the Ramrong and Curry here!

Fantastic Thai food. The mock duck is some of the best seitan I've ever had and the eggplant tempura is to die for. Great curry, great noodles, thai tea, thai coffee, this place has it all. Be prepared to be overwhelmed with flavor
Best Thai food we’ve ever had, and the nicest staff. Hands down our favorite restaurant!
Pretty good food
Best Thai restaurant in town, great pad thai, Tom kha gai and The thai iced tea is amazing
The Tofu Pad Thai is my absolute favorite. It always has the perfect amount of spicy.
Their mock duck curry is very good!

Amazing Thai food. I love all of their vegetarian options, most of them are actually (or can be turned into) vegan. Prices are fair and service is always good. My wife tried the sushi bar and she was quite happy with it.
Solid pick for good Thai food. I like the crispy pad thai, but many standard dishes offered in more than generous portions.
Was going to black dog for bbq but didnt want to wait.  This place was not a letdown by any means
Terrific food. Place has been here for a long time! 👍👍

I wanted to try something new that I've never had before. So I decided on Thai food, and I discovered this place. I ordered through Grub Hub, and it got here VERY fast. I got the Chicken Pad See You, and egg rolls. The egg rolls where very fresh, and tasted great. The main dish was even better. I definitely could tell whoever cooked this, is passionate about it. Definitely will eat again, and definitely would recommend. Great job!
Sushi is back.

We're lucky to have a lot of good Thai food in our town, but for me Siam Terrace rises above them all. Since day one their food is amazing, the staff and owners are extremely courteous and welcoming, and the atmosphere is cozy.
Great food, great service! Anything with the basil sauce will blow your mind. And the coconut ice cream!! Get the coconut ice cream. It's heaven. Sushi is the best in town.
I have never been disappointed with my orders here. Nice place and good food.
Nice Thai Pad...
Full menu selection including excellent sushi rolls. Great service. Nice ambiance. A pleasurable place to dine.
I got the “Thai fried rice” and it was the best fried rice I’d had in years! 10/10 my new go-to place!
Good Thai place with great food. They have my favorite crab rangoon. Got a wrong order once but it was so good I didnt care.

We love going to Siam Terrace, particularly for lunch.  Their lunch specials are a good deal, including a house salad with amazing sweet onion dressing.  You can customize your spice level on any dish.  Try the Lava Chicken!
Always delicious. One of my faves in C/U.
I eat here regularly! There are plenty of vegan options that are delicious. I recommend the mock duck basil and eggplant tempura.
Food is always great and they have options for everyone but the ripped chairs run the place down a bit. Overall would recommend eating here especially for the lunch special!
Great food and service.
Good food and service, I would like to see accessible guest Wi-Fi for a five star rating.
I ordered food It came vary quick. Veggie supreme was amazing.
Favorite Thai food in the area
Yummy food, great vegetarian options.  Lunch specials are well-priced but dine-in only.
Various types of Pad Thai. Spicy by request!
Great food
This place is AWESOME just go and eat..I will say this don't be foolish about your spiced levels unless your ready..😰😭😂😢😜😵
Great restaurant, fantastic owners, and always delicious food!
Excellent!

This restaurant doesn't have consistency in taste, the same soup that I ordered during the lunch time had different taste when I ordered during dinner time. The menu is also not same for online delivery and dine in.
Pot stickers and red curry were average. I ordered brown rice (cost extra), they gave me white.. If you're doing takeout, check your orders before leaving, or maybe just go to a different Thai place
The food is nice but the waitress was so rude when I asked for water without ice. Like why. I was in at Friday 26th April
Thai food, yeah, excellent. I love going here. The service was very friendly and attentive.
Easy to find downtown with some of the best food around. Ask your server for a recommendation if you aren't sure what to order.
I got curry with tofu and my date got crispy pad thai with tofu. Both were very greasy, far too much for my taste. I far prefer the Thai places in Campustown.
Food here is fantastic!

Great food! Lots of excellent options for east southeast Asia cuisine in the area, but the place stands out. Great diverse options and kind service. The location is nice tho not particularly pretty. Good for casual meals, low key date night, or take out! Give it a try, their menu will have whatever you might want!

Lovely lovely food! A spl Thai iced tea is the best drink I've had here. Amongst entrees, their special veggie fried rice (Chef's spl ) is great. THe original pad thai is amazing with appropriate aromatics and flavors.
Staff is great and the food is so so good! I have never had a bad experience.
Best pad Thai anywhere.
Food was delicious and staff were amazing. Great menu!

I found this place by accident, but was pleasantly surprised. I ordered their yellow curry. It same with a salad appetizer. The salad was nice, a little strong in terms of acidity, but nice flavor. Would recommend draining it prior to serving.  This place allows you to modulate your heat from 1-4. I chose '2' for the yellow curry to add a little spice but not losing the flavor of the yellow curry. When it came, it looked really good. Tasted nice. I would recommend leaving it at '1', as the spice slightly overpowered the curry.  Overall I would come back
I told everyone bangkok thai was the best in town, but this place just roasted me. Will come again.
1st time trying Thai food, glad it was here. Very good food. Stay low on the spice grid.
Always good

Lovely place with delicious food. My family had never tried Thai food before and was hesitant about having lunch at this place but at the end they loved it. The waiter noticed we weren't familiar with the menu and sent somebody that worked at the kitchen and spoke Spanish to help us. The atmosphere was great
SOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO DELICIOUS
Good food and an owner that cares.
Grear food, great staff and nice location.
Food was excellent as always, as was the service.  Best crab rangoon in town !
Food is fresh, service really good.
Great food, staff was very polite and efficient, the environment of the place is very calm.
Best Thai restaurant in town! Great food and great service!
Good food and good service.

The food is usually pretty good, altho last time I went they ran out of clean water glasses and cloth napkins. They were really busy and running behind. Everybody understood, I just think it was a little unexpected. I also think it could be a tad updated, but it is a community favorite regardless.

best Thai food in Champaign Urbana in our opinion. We have eaten there over 10 times and the food is always excellent. The wait staff is attentive and very helpful. We had a situation with a soup that my wife found to be a little too salty. The management staff immediately addressed our concerns and replace the soup with another less salty soup. Management staff handled it in a very professional way and seemed genually  concerned.
So good. One of my favorite places in town.
Crispy padthai  Best ever.
Best Thai place in town!
Great little place. Spicy food.
Best Pad Thai in town.
Delicious thai food! I highly recommend the Mock Duck Basil.
Great food
Try the lava chicken, great lunch spot

Great food, great service. The (vegetarian) pot stickers and tempura were delicious. The red curry and Pad Thai were delicious but if you like hot then ask for level 4. Level 2 was like nothing. Level 4 was nice and hot. They'll also give you pepper on the side in case 4 isn't hot enough. The molten lava cake was as beautifully plated as it was delicious.
Am a long time happy customer here - vest Thai in C-U.
Awesome Thai food
Delicious food, friendly staff who remember you and great lunch deals!
Very good food.

Okay so there might be reasons people order something OTHER than Mock Duck Curry, but I don't know why! The dish is simply one of the best vegan things I have encountered... anywhere! If you do order something other than Mock Duck Curry, you will find an expansive collection of options for all tastes.  Siam Terrace is the best place for Thai food in CU and a must visit.  The family-owned business creates a welcoming atmosphere.  They are friendly and responsive to the needs of customers. The staff, despite the turnover of a college town, is always well trained and courteous.  This place is perfect for date night, family meal or business lunch. They also do delivery and carry out options as well!  You should go there, like right now!

Siam terrace has wonderful thai food. A great deal of vegetarian options available. Eggplant tempura is a definite recommendation!  As a vegetarian, I liked the red curry fried rice. The thai curries are amazing and so is the thai ice tea. Portion sizes are such that one dish can completely fill one person.
good
Great service! Fairly priced food. Hands down the best Thai food I have ever had!
I really enjoyed the atmosphere and food. I'll definitely be back.
Pad  Thai great!

Been here multiple times, and the food has been excellent every time.  The portion sizes are generous, and there are multiple solid vegetarian and seafood options.  Last but not least, for dessert the sticky rice + mango/custard is excellent :)
Hands down the best Thai food in town!
My favorite Thai Restaurant in town. My meal favorites are the Tom Ka Ga soup, Pad Thai, Duck Noodle Soup, Chicken Lettuce Wrap appetizer, and their Crab Rangoon is the best I've ever had.
Best Thai in town.
I've had a lot of stuff on their menu and literally anything you order will be delicious
First time dining here. I had the Pad Thia and it was delicious. Very good service as well.
Great rangoons
delicious
The vegan mock duck curry is incredible.
Love it, my Thai go to. Iced tea is fantastic; never had anything I didn’t like from here.
Food was decent but the lunch prices are so great that I will be a regular.
First time eating Thai and it was wonderful!

I love their food. I've had great service about every single time, quick delivery, and the prices aren't bad for the amount of food you get. I usually get two meals out of a meal. I definitely recommend this place!
The food was good. They have good service.
Great food
I absolutely love this restaurant. I come every week and order the Lava Chicken. Highly recommend it to anyone who wants an amazing meal at a very reasonable price. The owners are also great!
Best Thai in town
The mock duck here is my favorite dish in all of Urbana.
Lunch special was very reasonably priced and the curry was delicious. Our serve Chris provided unmatched customer service that left us smiling and satisfied.
Reasonable pricing for high quality Thai cuisine.

They have delicious Thai food and can make it as spicy as you like it. The staff is attentive and friendly. Their iced coffee and tea are very good. The coconut ice cream is fantastic. Sometimes I go just for desert. It can get a little noisy some times but that's because it's usually full during lunch and dinner hours.
Excellent food!
The food was very tasty and the service was great. I had the Shrimp and Asparagus stir fry. The veggies were perfectly cooked and the brown sauce was excellent.
Great place to eat with awesome food and service. Only thing I did not like was that the tables were too close together.
Really good Thai food
Food is quite good. I've never tried anything that wasn't yummy. Service is sometimes a little iffy though. Just confusion about orders, and not coming by the table often enough.
A great evening,  food was fantastic
For Thai lovers!

I can always count on Siam Terrace to be a step above the other Thai places in town. Their noodles are a distinct pleasure, and the homemade coconut ice cream was among the tastiest desserts I have ever had! I can't wait to come back.
Excellent food at a very reasonable price!  Try the Lava Chicken on the lunch-specials menu.
The duck basil is divine
Excelkent service, very knowledgable waitress. Very good food.
The food here is absolutely delicious and not too pricey. Everything at the table looked and tasted great.
I had one noodle dish and the noodle was too soggy and felt like they kept the noddle for long time

One of the worst experience I've ever have. US-style Thai food, oilly, with its price unupdated online. (If you click "order online" you'll find that perhaps their menu hasn't been updated for years! )They also miscooked the food that a girl ordered as chicken to be vegetable. Would it cost a lot for the waiter to configure what have customers ordered? My review is not comprehensive, though. Pad Thai, and custard pudding are US-style, instead of traditional Thai style. Perhaps I should have ordered curry instead.
Good food and good ambience...

Loves the food. I'm a vegetarian, and this place has very good options for me. I ordered Fried rice in red curry which was super delicious. The green curry is also good. And the sticky rice with mango dessert is very good. There are a lot of good options for non vegetarians too. However, you may find it a bit expensive.
Excellent authentic food and great service, a smidge difficult to find the first time if your not local, but Worth it!!
The food was very good and flavorful!  Will be back!
Thai fried rice with Thai iced tea is where it's at!
High price
I'll be honest and say that I've never had a bad meal here but I've also never had a good one either.
Best Thai restaurant in town.
not bad..
Another hidden Gem in Paris! Food was very tasty and the ambience was lovely! Friendly staff! A bit pricey but soooo worth it!

I have never had Thai food before trying this place but I loved it. I like how you can chose how spicy or not your food can be. This is incredibly helpful for somebody that thinks mayo is on the spicy side.
Thai food is good. I miss the option of having sushi here.
The lava chicken is delicious!
My favorite place to go when Im in the area! Lots of delicious options and they have great vegan/vegetarian options.
Tasty Thai Food
Love this thai food so much!
Best Thai in town.  I frequently go here for lunch or get food to go.   Never disappointed.
Good food, but no more sushi.
Delicious food,  reasonably priced but our table of 6 got our meals out at very different times.  I could easily have finished my meal by the time the last person got theirs.

Excellent restaurant!  We discussed spicy heat levels of our orders with the server and were extremely pleased that our food was served exactly as we wanted.  We shared 2 entrees, fire cracker chicken and heaven duck curry.  Both were delicious.  And, we had the most delightful server - her friendliness and attentive service greatly enhanced an already wonderful meal.
The Pad thai and fake meat are delicious here. An expensive restaurant no doubt, but with great value for money.
The food here is SO good, especially the soups.
Always pick this place for a quick lunch. They have wonderful food for very reasonable prices. I like their yellow curry and their summer rolls with the sweet peanut sauce is the best!

Ate there many years ago and did not like any of the 3 entrees we ordered.. it was all plain and tasted funny. Then heard they have new owners? So decided to try some stir fried noodle dish yesterday and it did not taste good at all. But that's just my opinion. And no, i won't be going there ever again.. hope your experience goes better than mines!

The waitress argued with us when we tried to tell her that the food was unbearably spicy even for someone with a high spice tolerance. "It isn't spicy for me" she said. That's not the mark of good service.

Went tonight for dinner and ordered a thai green curry. It was extremely spicy, near inedible (and I'm Indian!). Although the server was gracious enough to ask if I wanted something else, the owner returned and literally reprimanded me for my order. One of the worst dining experiences. I will not be returning.
Good Thai food. sometime the service can be a bit delayed but good most of the time.
One of the best restaurants in Urbana downtown. The mango sticky rice is really tasty.
The place has a couple of options for vegetarians. The red curry fried rice and spicy fried rice are good.  Look out before you tip as they already add gratuity to your bill if you dine in.

Horrible service.  After our food was delivered, we never saw the wait staff again.  We waited 20 minutes and our water was never refilled and no one came back to check on us. We had to search out the wait staff and ask for the check just to leave.  I overheard other tables experiencing the same issues, staff was completely oblivious and seemed not to care.

I've been twice now, and have a third visit planned next week!  The soup, the Thai pastas, the California roll--it's all great!!  Service is friendly and speedy as well.  If there's a cold wind, be careful where you sit, because there can be quite the breeze when the door's opened!  Also, not sure how this garnered the $$.  Most of their lunch specials are less than $7 and include a house salad.
Poor service. Cold draft running through the store. They forgot our order, and didn't even seem to care. Would not recommend.

Taken by friends for a Friday night dinner. The Summer rolls were very good as was the Crab Rangoon and both were reasonably priced for appetizers. The Curry dish ordered was declared superb and the 2 Chicken dishes were flavorful and nicely done. Service was very good with the decor and atmosphere being casual and comfortable.

I ordered delivery. My pad kee mao did not appear to have ever met basil and chili paste, which is pretty sad since those are the primary flavorings.  It also was less than half noodles by volume.  Either they were being sloppy and forgot ingredients or have the worst recipe I've ever tried.  The cashew nut was okay but nothing special.  Overall I'm not impressed.

Siam Terrace has very great deals on lunch specials. The decor should be updated. But, I'm there to eat the food, not the wall decorations. I'm always satisfied when I got there for meals, definitely a recommended location!

If you are looking for great sushi on a budget, I would recommend Siam Terrace over KoFusion. The sushi is fresh, and the menu also offers main dishes that are delicious. The restaurant is family owned, so support this great place!

I paid $15 for a the Salmon Ginger dish and was VERY disappointed. The dish came out as a salmon steak in the middle of a pool of ginger sauce. The flavors were good, but the salmon was very tough and chewy. I debated the freshness of the fish and lost any confidence in the kitchen's ability to prepare fish.  Not once did any of the employees ask me how my food was. It was not a busy night, there were maybe 3 other tables seated while I was there. Additionally, the Salmon Ginger was one of the  "Recommended" food items on the menu.
Ask for mango curry chicken... it is the best I ever had.
